page.title: 10CHURCH STRETTON WILDLIFE
page.content:
Wildlife in Church Stretton varies quite a lot due to the moorland of the Long Mynd and the dense woodland.
On the moorland there is not much animal life apart from{adders, grass {snakes and farm animals.}But there are a lot of birds of prey. The most common of these is the{buzzard}which eats mice, voles, rats, young hares and rabbits, frogs, snakes and large insects. The less common birds of prey are the{sparrow hawk, kestrel and {merlin.} In the woodland there is more animal life including foxes, grey squirrels, badgers and wood mice.
